.TH COMPOSITEALPHA 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-shapetools" "SmartMet Tools"
.SH NAME
compositealpha \- replace the alpha channel of an image with a mask image
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B compositealpha
.I inputimage
.I maskimage
.I outputimage
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B compositealpha
reads
.I inputimage
and
.IR maskimage ,
which must have identical pixel dimensions, and writes a new image to
.I outputimage
where each output pixel takes its colour from
.I inputimage
and its alpha from the intensity of the corresponding pixel in
.IR maskimage .
A bright pixel in the mask therefore yields an opaque output pixel
and a dark mask pixel a transparent one.
.PP
The output image format is selected from the suffix of
.IR outputimage .
The output is written with palette and alpha enabled.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I inputimage
The image whose colour values are kept.
.TP
.I maskimage
The image whose intensity is used as the new alpha channel.
.TP
.I outputimage
The output filename. The format is determined by the suffix.
.SH EXAMPLES
Build a transparent map by masking a base image with a separately
rendered alpha mask:
.PP
.RS 4
compositealpha base.png alpha.png result.png
.RE
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
